this last week✨We spent an amazing week here at @puravistaecovillas 
in Pavones, Costa Rica!

My mind is blown by the raw nature we experienced here. The wildlife was incredible, monkeys everyday, rare animals, birds of unique kinds, bugs, & gorgeous plant life! 
It was an epic time as a family & a sweet 🥰 time as we celebrated 8 years married! Plus we got some great waves & beach times too.
Thankful for fun times with kind people, who shared their beautiful culture & who truly shared the “pura vida” life! 
Can’t wait to come again!

node.text: Yesterday was crazy. We smelt smoke and checked outside and saw a fire getting started right near the house. 20 minute later we evacuated! That was a wild experience. Thankful no houses burnt down and more importantly all the people the area were safe! Thanks to the local fire safety crew for getting it under control!

node.text:
Hey friends! Sooo I removed my instagram and FB from my phone. 

Here’s why. The privacy you don’t have from these platforms is terrible. 
They have access to EVERYTHING.... I’ll let you do your own research if this concerns you. 

Also I just wanted to spend less time on them and be more present with my life and it’s working out great!!! 

I find it crazy how addicting it can be. Do your fingers just magnet to these platforms even when you may not want them to?! Mine sure do...

Also, I get disappointed when I’m with friends or family and they just zone out and disappear from hanging out with us into online social World. They are just gone... 

Anyway It’s been amazing!!! I wish I did it sooner!!! So I had to share this idea with y’all so you to may experience the freedom and goodness of just owning your time and life! 
Lots of ❤️✌🏽

node.title: I removed my social off my phone 🤗❌📱

Friends of Bethany is now the Beautifully Flawed Foundation! 🎉

As our foundation has grown over the years, we felt a passion to widen the platform for others to shine their stories of hope and impact the world around them. I’m excited to see the growth of this non profit and continue to support and be apart of the amazing retreats we’ve been doing for years now!!!

Now known as the Beautifully Flawed Foundation, more opportunities are being created to partner with and highlight the many incredible people impacted by our programs. The name may have changed but not the focus: with the mission of offering hope to those impacted by the brokenness of his world to overcome through Jesus Christ.

Check out @beautifullyflawed_foundation to learn more, or head to their website beautifullyflawedfoundation.com! #friendsofbethany #beautifullyflawedfoundation

node.text:
Merry Christmas season!!! I hope you and your loved ones are hanging in there!

Adam and I want to share life empowerment and encourage YOU in a more intentional way. This has sure been a tough year, and it got me thinking about the difficult times of my life and how it has been my community and faith that uplift and encourage me to keep going. We want to do the same for you so we just launched a new private Facebook group that will be a place of encouragement and intentional living to empower you and create a community of positivity!

We’ll be diving deep into Unstoppable Living by digging into some of the tough and essential topics of life, encouraging you in the progress of your goals, and sharing in monthly live Q&As with Adam and me. This is a motivating and uplifting community to empower and support YOU
💥

Our first live Q&A will be this Wednesday, December 16th, so join TODAY to participate! Join the group here: bit.ly/UnstoppableLiving #linkinbio

Dips & sauces make food so fun and delicious, so that is where I often start in the kitchen! This is the first time I’ve made this green onion dip with no recipe. That’s my style, I like to wing it. And I’ll show you how! Green onions are kinda like that ‘what do I do with you’ food for me but I enjoyed them in this creamy dip! It’s yummy on crackers, veggies to dip, wraps, sandwiches, and more!

Check out the recipe on my blog: https://bit.ly/2NKlhNC #linkinbio

this last week✨We spent an amazing week here at @puravistaecovillas 
in Pavones, Costa Rica!

My mind is blown by the raw nature we experienced here. The wildlife was incredible, monkeys everyday, rare animals, birds of unique kinds, bugs, & gorgeous plant life! 
It was an epic time as a family & a sweet 🥰 time as we celebrated 8 years married! Plus we got some great waves & beach times too.
Thankful for fun times with kind people, who shared their beautiful culture & who truly shared the “pura vida” life! 
Can’t wait to come again!

node.text:
You CAN live UNSTOPPABLE. 

Ok I’m gonna get nerdy with a mini pep talk here… 

Living UNSTOPPABLE Is not about being perfect and having it together at each and every moment. But more about having the resiliency to get back on your “board” when life throws you off. It’s making the needed adjustment when change is inevitable. 
You CAN adapt when times get chaotic. You CAN  choose a healthy mindset. You CAN overcome your fears. You CAN stand for truth. You CAN live in faith when all else fails. 
You CAN make the most of what you’ve got every day! You CAN get back on your board… 
I’m cheering you on to live unstoppable. 💪🏽

For more “pep talks” join me in UNSTOPPABLE living at my website Bethanyhamilton.com

The sun rises and sets each day. It’s something we can count on. Like the sun, I count on good prevailing as well. 
Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good. Romans 12:21

I always have hope regardless of how dark the world may seem. I believe good will prevail! 
My mind is set on goodness and truth. My hope is in God above. My peace is in the greater promises set before us. 

I hope you can find your hope and peace each day as life goes forward regardless of what the world may throw at us❤️❤️❤️

What foundations are you living your life based on? 

Health~ Togetherness ~ Quality time~ Love~ Self worth ~ Faith! 
These are just a few foundations we will continue to build our family up with!!!
Foundations that I hope will lead our children to thrive in this world. 
I love family moments like this… All of us getting movement in, in nature while sharing quality time! 
I’ll be honest… I did have to coerce the boys to come outside with us, but once we got going they had a fun time😜nerf bullets flying and some hill runs with me! 

Life has choices each day. Adam, my husband, has been in a mindset to “make the most of each day” and it’s contagious. He’s so great about setting the phone down and focusing on us and it’s admirable. 

We get to choose how we live our life, our foundations, focuses, boundaries, intentions.
What you choose is up to you! Choose wise❤️

#Health #unstoppable #family #bepresent
